President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Stephen E. Biegun for the position of Deputy Secretary of State. Biegun currently serves as the United States Special Representative for North Korea at the Department of State, where he oversees all US policy on North Korea. Prior to his current role, Biegun worked as Vice President of International Governmental Relations for Ford Motor Company. He has extensive experience in both the Executive and Legislative Branches of government, having served as national security advisor to Senate Majority Leader Bill Frist and as Chief of Staff of the United States Senate Committee on Foreign Relations. Biegun has also held positions at the United States House of Representatives Committee on Foreign Affairs and the White House National Security Council. He is a graduate of the University of Michigan and is a member of the Council on Foreign Relations. Biegun has served on the boards of various organizations, including the National Bureau of Asian Research, the U.S.-ASEAN Business Council, the U.S.-Russia Foundation for Economic Development and the Rule of Law, and Freedom House.